This command helps you efficiently develop your Appwrite functions on your local machine. Any changes to your function code are instantly reflected without waiting for them to build. This is because when you develop a function locally, it hot reloads your code, provided you've initiated it with the `appwrite run functions` command. When developing your Appwrite function locally, it will receive [headers](/docs/products/functions/develop#headers) like when you develop a function in the Console.

